# GitHub Personal Access Token (Optional but Recommended)
# 
# Without token: Shows only PUBLIC data
# - Public repositories only
# - Public PRs and issues only
# - Limited API rate (60 requests/hour)
#
# With token: Shows PUBLIC + PRIVATE data
# - All repositories (public + private)
# - All PRs and issues (including in private repos)
# - Higher API rate (5000 requests/hour)
# - More accurate language statistics
#
# How to create your token:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Name: "Portfolio Website"
# 4. Select scopes:
#    ✅ repo (full control of private repositories)
#    ✅ read:user (read user profile data)
# 5. Click "Generate token"
# 6. Copy the token (starts with ghp_...) and paste below
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit this file! It's in .gitignore

GITHUB_TOKEN=
